{{Infobox protected area | name = Campo de los Alisos National Park | alt_name = Parque Nacional Campo de los Alisos | iucn_category = II | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | photo_width = 280 | map = Argentina | relief = yes | map_alt = Location within Argentina | map_caption = Location within Argentina | map_width = 120 | location = [[Tucumán Province]], [[Argentina]] | nearest_city = [[Concepción (Tucumán)|Concepción]] | coords = {{coord|27|13|S|65|58|W|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <!-- source:kolossus-frwiki --> | area_ha = 17000 | established = {{start date|1995|8|9}}<ref name=decree1>{{cite Argentine law|l=24526|date=1995-09-12|bo=28226|p=1|sdate=1995-08-09}}</ref> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = | url = }} The '''Campo de los Alisos National Park''' ({{lang-es|Parque Nacional Campo de los Alisos}}, literally "Field of [[Alder]]s") is a [[National parks of Argentina|federal protected area]] in [[Tucumán Province]], [[Argentina]]. Established on 9 August 1995,<ref name=decree1/> it houses a representative sample of the southern [[Yungas]] montane jungle [[biodiversity]] in good state of conservation.
Located in the [[Chicligasta Department]] on the eastern slope of the ''Nevados del Aconquija'', the park has an area of {{convert|17000|ha|km2 sqmi|abbr=on}}. The Aconquija mountains are the southern extension of the [[Calchaquíes Valleys]], the western first steps raising from the [[Gran Chaco]] plain into the [[Argentine Northwest|Northwest]] region. Annual rainfall here oscillates between {{convert|100|-|200|mm|abbr=on}}
==Biodiversity== [[Flora (plants)|Flora]] and [[fauna (animals)|fauna]] vary considerably with the different heights, from a jungle at lower levels to snow-covered mountainous terrain at {{convert|5000|m|abbr=on}} <!-- there is much more in the official page, but I can't translate the technical terms! -->
