{{Infobox journal | title = Proceedings of the Combustion Institute | cover = | editor = Volker Sick and Alison Tomlin | discipline = [[Combustion phenomena]] | former_names = Symposium (International) on Combustion; Symposium on Combustion and Flame, and Explosion Phenomena; Proceedings of the Symposium on Combustion | abbreviation = Proc. Combust. Inst. | publisher = [[Elsevier]] | country = | frequency = biannual | history = 1948-today | openaccess = Option | license = | impact = 5.336 | impact-year = 2017 | website = https://www.journals.elsevier.com/proceedings-of-the-combustion-institute | link1 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/15407489 | link1-name = Online access | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1540-7489 | eISSN = }} The '''''Proceedings of the Combustion Institute''''' are the proceedings of the biennial Combustion Symposium put on by [[The Combustion Institute]]. The publication contains the most significant contributions in fundamentals and applications [[fundamental research]] of combustion science [[combustion phenomena]]. Research papers and invited topical reviews are included on topics of reaction kinetics, soot, PAH and other large molecules, diagnostics, laminar flames, turbulent flames, heterogenous combustion, spray and droplet combustion, detonations, explosions & supersonic combustion, fire research, stationary combustion systems, internal combustion engine and gas turbine combustion, and new technology concepts. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Volker Sick ([[University of Michigan]]) and Alison Tomlin ([[University of Leeds]]).
